# Agent Workstation Rules

This workstation uses `~/.agents` as the canonical source for reusable rules, hooks, prompts, and source mirrors.

## Required Shared Rules

Read and follow:

- `~/.agents/rules/operating-principles.md`
- `~/.agents/rules/codebase-exploration.md`
- `~/.agents/rules/reliability-observability.md`
- `~/.agents/rules/secrets-and-safety.md`

## Skills

Reusable skills are installed under `~/.claude/skills` from the repository skill projections. `~/.agents/skills` is intentionally managed empty after the duplicate-skill cleanup.

## Adapter Boundary

Do not assume Codex hook events exist in Claude. Use the shared rules and skills first, then Claude-native capabilities where available.
